{
  "doc_id": "38376",
  "text": "Physical activity and exercise can affect the occurrence of cancers through reduction of fat tissues, hormonal concentration and energy balance [CITATION_1] . Friedenreich showed that sedentary lifestyle increased risk of colorectal cancer [CITATION_2] . Moreover, studies showed that cigarette smoking habit and high number of cigarettes were risk factors of stomach and colorectal cancers [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Also, mental disorders such as stress, poor sleeping pattern, environmental risks and drug abuse are important contributors on cancer development. Therefore, promote a healthy lifestyle should be continuous and regular.",
